# Icons (`app/icons.js`)

Do **not** fabricate or guess SVG path markup. Agents are not reliable sources for icon geometry.

When a new icon is needed:

1. Add a **skeleton entry** to `ICONS` with metadata only — leave `markup` empty or as a placeholder the user will replace.
2. Set `viewBox`, `name` (Icônes collection id), and `attribution` when sourcing from Material Icons.
3. Wire up usage elsewhere (`data-icon="…"` in HTML or `createIcon()` in JS) if needed.
4. **Stop** and tell the user which skeleton was added so they can paste path markup from [Icônes — Material Icons (Round)](https://icones.js.org/collection/ic?s=info&variant=Round).

Prefer `{ ref: "existing-icon" }` when an existing icon already fits — no new entry required.

## Skeleton example

```javascript
"my-icon": {
  viewBox: "0 0 24 24",
  markup: ``,
  attribution: ICON_ATTRIBUTIONS.materialIcons,
  name: "round-my-icon", // Icônes id — user fills in markup
},
```

## Do not

- Invent `<path>` or other SVG elements from memory
- Copy approximate paths from training data
- Add fully populated icon entries unless the user explicitly pasted the source SVG markup in the chat
